                                    <h5 class="card-title">General Information</h5>
                                    <p class="card-text">
                                        The rose is a woody perennial flowering plant of the genus Rosa, in the family Rosaceae. 
                                        There are over three hundred species and tens of thousands of cultivars. They form a group 
                                        of plants that can be erect shrubs, climbing, or trailing, with stems that are often armed 
                                        with sharp prickles.
                                    </p>
                                    
                                    <div class="row mt-4">
                                        <div class="col-md-6">
                                            <h6>Physical Characteristics</h6>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Thorny stems with compound leaves</li>
                                                <li>Flowers typically have 5 petals</li>
                                                <li>Colors range from white to deep red</li>
                                                <li>Strong, pleasant fragrance</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="col-md-6">
                                            <h6>Growth Habits</h6>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Blooms from spring to fall</li>
                                                <li>Requires regular pruning</li>
                                                <li>Can live for decades with proper care</li>
                                                <li>Attracts bees and butterflies</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

